<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Asian Games official in stable condition after being hit by stray hammer throw]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/oct/02/asian-games-2023-official-hit-by-hammer-throw-broken-leg-stable-condition]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T23:57:27Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ac0ee44b3700aeb63737843c5253ba4d217f457e/0_285_6941_4167 /master/6941.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=09add8eb1ba9ceddb18b44aff7398a35&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;杭州亚运官员黄钦华腿部被铁锤击中后被担架抬去就医，中国。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;杭州亚运会上，一名田径官员被误扔的铁锤击中，腿部骨折，严重流血，目前生命体征稳定。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六科威特选手阿里·赞卡维 (Ali Zankawi) 在中国东部城市拥挤的奥林匹克体育场举行的男子链球决赛中排队等待投球。但锤子并没有直接飞到外场，而是从侧面低飞到右侧，砸在了坐着的技术官员的腿上。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/sep/29/lee-kang-in-targets-a-prize-greater-than-glory-in-the-asian-games&quot;>;李强仁的目标是在亚运会上获得比荣耀更重要的奖品&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;赞卡维看上去很惊恐，他冲过去，官员的右腿开始喷血。当赞卡维冲过去检查时，62岁的官员黄钦华做了个鬼脸，头晕目眩地摇晃着，鲜血从伤口中喷涌而出。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几秒钟之内，赞卡维就用他巨大的双手和力量在黄的身上临时绑上了止血带。大腿并止血。医护人员很快将黄某用止血带用担架抬走，送往附近医院。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“20时15分到达医院，经诊断为右开放性下胫腓骨骨折， ”奥运会发言人徐德庆在周日的新闻发布会上说。 “目前他的生命体征稳定。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;52f7666fd6df7cb3d00534a7c3fad774b331c173&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/52f7666fd6df7cb3d00534a7c3fad774b331c173/0 _0_5001_3334/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;科威特选手赞卡维·阿里在 2023 年亚运会上的表现。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;科威特选手赞卡维·阿里在 2023 年亚运会上的表现。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Lee Jin-man/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption >; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;据路透社目击者称，赛后赞卡维看上去很震惊，有人看到他在询问官员的情况。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;决赛由中国选手王琪获胜。赞卡维获得第八名，但仍然取得了赛季最好成绩 67.57 m，这是他在第二轮投掷失误之前投出的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;正如田径比赛中常见的那样，裁判坐在距离笼状网几米的地方围绕投掷圈，运动员旋转并投掷。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是，7.26 公斤飞行金属球的力量和速度意味着网只能稍微缓冲链球的飞行，而不能阻止它。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; p>; &lt;p>;田径运动中的网设计得相对宽松，以防止链球和铁球在失误后反弹到运动员身上。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;中国社交媒体平台微博的许多用户，事件发生在微博上周日的趋势称，应改进安全协议，为官员提供更好的保护。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 08:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Let’s have that fight’: McCarthy and Gaetz go to war over shutdown deal]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/01/matt-gaetz-kevin-mccarthy-house-speaker-shutdown-deal]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T17:36:12Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/72c988e754c566187c1a1f2265a8b654d4d0ab37/0_76_6667_4002 /master/6667.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=32442053a3208dcc8dfbc80be9de596a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;凯文·麦卡锡在众议院通过一项为政府提供资金的权宜措施后发表讲话。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;共和党人之间对&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/30/us-government-shutdown-congress-senate-kevin-mccarthy&quot;>;两党协议&lt;/周日，避免政府关门的行动陷入了公开的政治战争，一名右翼国会议员表示，他将采取行动驱逐凯文·麦卡锡和&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct /01/kevin-mccarthy-us-government-shutdown-republican-speaker&quot;>;陷入困境的众议院议长&lt;/a>;坚称他会生存。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/30/us-government-shutdown-congress-senate-kevin-mccarthy&quot;>;“这是个好消息”：拜登签署权宜之计资金避免美国关闭的法案&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“我们需要撕掉创可贴。我们需要新的值得信赖的领导层继续前进，”佛罗里达州众议员马特·盖茨 (Matt Gaetz) 告诉 CNN 的国情咨文，并表示他将在未来几天内提出“辞职动议”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦卡锡盖茨说，他谎称与民主党达成“一项秘密协议”，后来为乌克兰提供了妥协协议之外的资金，并误导了共和党人与反对派合作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该法案保留周六晚上，众议院以 335 票对 91 票通过了为期 47 天的政府资助计划，其中 209 名民主党人与 126 名共和党人一起支持。该法案在参议院以 88 比 9 获得通过，并由乔·拜登签署。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拜登周日在白宫发表讲话时表示，该法案将资金延长至 11 月 17 日，其中包括 160 亿美元的救灾援助，防止了“一场不必要的危机”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是，拜登说：“事实是，我们一开始就不应该在这里。现在是结束危机治理并在国会兑现诺言的时候了。我完全希望议长能够信守承诺，确保获得帮助乌克兰抵御侵略所需的支持。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当被问及是否希望麦卡锡勇敢地面对极端分子时，拜登回答道：“我希望演讲者的这次经历是个人启示。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦卡锡回击盖茨，称他是一个“更感兴趣的是获得电视采访”而不是维持政府运转的表演家。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;“我会活下去，”麦卡锡告诉哥伦比亚广播公司的“面对国家”节目。 “你知道，这是马特的私事。他想迫使我们关闭，甚至威胁他自己的地区，那里的所有军人都不会得到报酬。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“……就这样吧。来吧。让我们结束这一切，然后开始治理。如果他因为试图迫使我们关闭而感到不安，而我确保政府没有关闭，那么我们就来一场战斗吧。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;c22df06e5fe04cc38f175117fb506d9a353ce1f3&quot;>; &lt;img src= &quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/c22df06e5fe04cc38f175117fb506d9a353ce1f3/0_217_4650_2790/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;马特·盖茨在众议院台阶上与媒体成员交谈。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;马特·盖茨在众议院台阶上与媒体成员交谈。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Nathan Howard/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/span>; &lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Nathan Howard/Getty Images盖茨表示，他将不再坚持一月份达成的支持麦卡锡的协议，以换取包括在联邦资金问题上采取强硬立场的让步。该协议包括放宽规则，允许单个议员提出退出动议，这是罢免议长程序的开始。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“凯文·麦卡锡最终成为众议院议长的唯一途径是下周的重点是民主党是否会保释他，他们可能会的，”盖茨说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我已经受够了凯文·麦卡锡。我们在一月份达成协议，允许他担任议长，我不再拥有他了，因为他不说实话。因此，如果民主党人想通过保释凯文·麦卡锡来拥有他，我无法阻止他们。但随后他将成为他们的发言人，而不是我的发言人。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦卡锡需要 218 票才能保住他的职位。一些资深民主党人表示，他们不会投票拯救他，而是会支持少数党领袖哈基姆·杰弗里斯。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;纽约的亚历山大·奥卡西奥-科尔特斯 (Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez) 告诉 CNN，“凯文·麦卡锡是一个非常软弱的演说家”，他说她会支持盖茨的动议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦卡锡“显然已经失去了对党团的控制。他把美国和数百万美国人带到了悬崖边，等到最后一刻才让政府继续开放，但即便如此，他也只延长了 4[7] 天。我们将在 11 月份回到这个地方。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;杰弗里斯周六对记者表示，该协议代表着“右翼极端分子的彻底投降”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;共和党人忠于麦卡锡的人还攻击盖茨和右翼众议院自由核心小组，因为他们承诺驱逐议长，这是“破坏性的”。本星期。 “他们是我们必须与众议院民主党人合作的原因。这不是凯文·麦卡锡的错，而是马特·盖茨的错。他的嘴巴很粗鲁，而且坦率地说，是两面派。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;演讲者和盖茨之间的关系达到了新低&lt;a href=&quot;https://thehill.com/homenews/house/4228092-mccarthy-周四的一次会议上，gaetz-get-into-testy-exchange-over-anti-gaetz-paid-post/&quot;>;激烈对抗&lt;/a>;。盖茨指责麦卡锡策划了一场针对他的社交媒体运动，发言人表示，他对这位国会议员的评价不够高，无法这样做。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周日，盖茨坚称“这是为了让凯文·麦卡锡信守诺言，这与任何个人恩怨无关”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;盖茨声称麦卡锡达成了一项“秘密协议”，承诺提出一项独立法案，继续资助乌克兰击退俄罗斯入侵者的努力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;许多共和党人反对美国帮助支付战争费用。盖茨说：“无论你如何看待[乌克兰的资金]，它都应该接受公开审查[和]分析，而不是幕后交易，所以我必须在本周提出一项动议，要求腾出反对议长麦卡锡的机会。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;盖茨在美国广播公司 (ABC) 上表示，他预计不会获得足够的选票来立即罢免麦卡锡，“但我可能会在第 15 次投票之前获得这些选票”，暗指 1 月份选举议长所需的时间。&lt;/p >; &lt;p>;“我是不懈的，我将继续追求这个目标，”盖茨说。 “如果所有美国人民都看到的是，统治他们的是一个单一政党，总是由拜登、麦卡锡和杰弗里斯政府在支出方面做出决定性决定，那么我正在为未来的初选播下种子，让共和党人在选举中表现更好。华盛顿。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拜登的预算总监沙兰达·杨 (Shalanda Young) 指责共和党将政府推向关闭的边缘，并敦促国会采取更长远的眼光。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们需要从今天开始，以确保美国人民不会采取这种边缘政策和最后一刻的焦虑，”她告诉美国广播公司。 “让我们做好我们的工作，避免这种情况再次发生。让我们在这 47 天结束时得到全年资金账单。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 07:52:01 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels actor Jake Abraham dies aged 56]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/oct/01/lock-stock-and-two-smoking-barrels-actor-jake-abraham-dies-aged-56]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T22:15:12Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/20fb75b598dcd95635eed695594cae4a3ae1e56a/242_291_868_521 /master/868.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=bc343392e831e47aae6a052e2e1b5ea5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;杰克·亚伯拉罕&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;演员杰克·亚伯拉罕，因在盖·里奇的锁中扮演的角色而闻名，斯托克和两个大烟桶去世，享年 56 岁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在英国黑帮电影中扮演迪恩的亚伯拉罕于 7 月份透露了自己的前列腺癌诊断结果，并表示正在接受姑息治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;这位出生于利物浦的演员的其他角色包括 1991 年第 4 频道的剧集《GBH》以及电影《Mean Machine》和《Formula 51》。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;曾与杰克多次合作的利物浦剧院导演兼制片人比尔·埃尔姆斯 (Bill Elms) 告诉我们利物浦回声报：“我很高兴与杰克合作制作了几部我共同制作的节目，《穿越默西河的两便士》和《列侬的班卓琴》，他是一位出色的演员，一位出色的公司成员，深受许多人的喜爱。整个行业。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们将遗憾地怀念他。我对杰克有很多美好的回忆，他总是那么乐观，和他在一起很有趣。我钦佩他公开自己的病情，这将为许多其他人带来改变并拯救生命。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是非常悲伤的一天。安息吧，并向他的朋友和家人表达我的爱。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;亚伯拉罕此前告诉《回声报》，他在长期患病后去看医生后被诊断出患有癌症。后来癌症扩散到他身体的其他部位，肿瘤在他的脊柱、臀部和膀胱中发展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我正在工作，但我感觉不舒服。我正在克服这些魔咒，当你感觉不到自己、没有精力、浑身酸痛时，”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“是什么让我去看医生并接受了治疗。 PSA（前列腺特异性抗原）测试显示我的尿液中带血。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我接受了测试，最终进入了皇家。他说：“你得了癌症，我非常非常抱歉。”他说我已经拥有这把枪很多年了，也许四年了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;亚伯拉罕在里奇 1998 年的经典作品中扮演的角色是两个无能的小偷之一，他们被派去偷一对古董猎枪。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 06:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Little sign of Tory unity as factions jostle on first day of conference]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/oct/01/little-sign-of-tory-unity-as-factions-jostle-on-first-day-of-conference]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T21:30:19Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/3e549716dfd74c6f92df7e350f8c7e5e5cfed1b3/233_0_4293_2577 /master/4293.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=33fa6163d4a8e383e3456bd706566298&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Rishi Sunak 在曼彻斯特保守党会议上发表演讲时指向观众的两侧&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;里希·苏纳克 (Rishi Sunak) 正在努力将分裂的政党团结在一起，因为保守党会议的第一天，统一战线的努力就崩溃了，陷入了在税收、文化战争和争夺下一任保守党领袖的斗争中的敌对团体。&lt;/p >; &lt;p>;在他自己精心策划的评论中，首相利用采访和曼彻斯特集会将自己描绘成一个变革的人物，在琐碎的政治纷争之外做出艰难但必要的长期选择。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;由于苏纳克继续拒绝透露 HS2 是否会延伸到该市，这次活动已经面临被蒙上阴影的风险，远离主要会议舞台的各种吵闹的保守党派系争先恐后地发表意见。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/oct/01/vultures-circle-around-sunak-conservative-party-conference-manchester ”秃鹰在苏纳克周围盘旋，代表们目光呆滞地看着|约翰·克雷斯（John Crace）&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;在这也许是当天最严厉的评论中，长期以来被视为保守党后起之秀的蒂斯谷市长本·侯辰 (Ben Houchen) 表示，他不会押注自己的经济。党赢得下一次选举。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“目前还不行，”他在一次边缘活动中说道，并补充说苏纳克需要“采取更多措施，为人们提供投票保守党的借口”。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;苏纳克也面临着越来越大的压力，要求他在选举前承诺减税，这是十号议员想要做的事情，但考虑到利兹·特拉斯无资金减税的财政影响，苏纳克的做法极其谨慎。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;超过 30 名主要支持特拉斯的保守党议员签署了一项极不寻常且近乎叛逆的承诺，表示他们不会投票支持秋季增税声明，上级部长迈克尔·戈夫呼吁削减个人税。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;“我希望在下一次选举之前看到税收负担减轻，”戈夫在接受《天空周日》特雷弗·菲利普斯节目采访时强调，即使是内阁部长在政策问题上也有自由职业的程度——尽管他后来略有反悔，告诉英国新闻通货膨胀需要首先下降。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着苏纳克在选举前减税的压力越来越大，财政大臣杰里米·亨特将宣布计划对那些“甚至不去找工作”的人实施更严格的福利限制.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着政府试图节省福利开支，财政大臣将在周一的讲话中承诺对福利制裁制度进行新的改革。他还将宣布将生活工资改为每小时 11 英镑。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，税收争议的焦点可能会在周一出现，届时特拉斯将在一年后的一次边缘活动中发表自己的演讲。特拉斯在短暂担任首相期间召开了灾难性的党内会议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;特拉斯呼吁 10 号议员“重振保守党价值观”，这是一些保守党议员敢于直言不讳的又一个迹象。并将公司税削减至 19%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;预计她还将要求放宽规划规则，以促进房屋建设并重启水力压裂，而这两者都不是政府政策。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;工党指责特拉斯要重振 12 个月前导致经济崩溃的幻想经济学”，并呼吁苏纳克否定她的想法。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在接受 BBC One 的周日采访时，劳拉·库恩斯伯格 (Laura Kuenssberg) 总理拒绝承诺征税苏纳克表示，“我们能为劳动人民提供的最佳减税措施就是将通货膨胀率减半。”苏纳克的表现有时有些暴躁，他辩称，他对不经选举就职，然后放弃大部分税收感到轻松。保守党的 2019 年宣言，因为他本能地了解公众想要什么。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我很清楚英国人民的优先事项是什么，”他说。 “我将着手为他们提供服务。这就是我要带来的改变。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这次会议已经看到了来自党内右翼的政策挑战，有时还夹杂着部长们公开争夺职位，试图将自己定位为如果保守党输掉选举，苏纳克的继任者。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在会议之前，商务大臣凯米·巴德诺克和内政大臣苏埃拉·布雷弗曼利用报纸采访重申他们呼吁英国退出欧盟人权公约（ECHR）——再次不是政府政策。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;新保守党是一个由右倾后座议员组成的文化战争友好团体，他们在周日公布的民意调查显示，他们说，大多数选民和绝大多数保守党选民支持退出欧洲人权法院。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周一，该团体将举行集会，敦促苏纳克通过五项宣言承诺，包括撤销欧洲人权法院以及减税、大规模削减移民、减少上大学的年轻人数量以及禁止“学校中的性别意识形态”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这表明美国式的文化战争问题已日益成为美国主流。新保守党联合创始人之一、保守党后座议员米里亚姆·凯茨(Miriam Cates)利用周日的一次边缘活动，在没有任何证据的情况下辩称网络色情是人们变性的驱动因素。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这这是轶事，但你看到很多跨性别女性，所以男性，说是跨性别色情导致他们进入跨性别舞台，”她说。 “所以我毫不怀疑互联网上这种极端、暴力和非常令人不安的色情内容与此有很大关系。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;大量议员甚至部长推动自己的议程，引起了政府对大选中可能出现不守纪律和草率信息的担忧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;安德鲁·米切尔 (Andrew Mitchell) 坚称，他个人并不认为纪律不严是党内的一个问题，但国际发展组织部长警告“人们不要在舞台上打扮自己，炫耀他们五颜六色的羽毛”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他说：“当你即将投入战斗时，你不要开始与司令。你继续准备赢得这场战斗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为该国或议会中的保守党不会在我们的国家和需要的时候容忍这种自我放纵。我们的政党赢得下次选举。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 06:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Rory McIlroy fights back tears after Europe beat USA to win Ryder Cup]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/oct/01/rory-mcilroy-fights-back-tears-after-europe-beat-usa-to-win-ryder-cup-report]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T16:14:15Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/8d070920d9820c76ec2c87ae487d87e8e3f9ef38/0_109_4753_2852 /master/4753.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=7962f044de665086e416357ae6ed0a1c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;欧洲队队长卢克·唐纳德（中）与罗里·麦克罗伊（右）一起举起莱德杯奖杯。 &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;罗里·麦克罗伊在贡献职业生涯最佳表现帮助欧洲重夺莱德杯后，强忍着喜悦的泪水，而不是失望。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦克罗伊单打战胜萨姆·伯恩斯确保他赢得四场比赛这是卢克·唐纳德的球队第一次在两年一度的比赛中连续第七次客场击败美国队。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;维克多·霍夫兰 (Viktor Hovland) 在乔恩·拉姆 (Jon Rahm) 抓鸟之前击败科林·森川 (Collin Morikawa) 取得了第一分第 18 名，在与世界排名第一的斯科特·舍夫勒 (Scottie Scheffler) 的首场比赛中抢得半分。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /sport/live/2023/oct/01/ryder-cup-2023-europe-v-usa-day- Three-singles-live&quot;>;2023 年莱德杯：欧洲对阵美国，第三天单打 - 直播&lt;/a>;&lt; /p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;帕特里克·坎特利随后顶住了贾斯汀·罗斯的追击，缩小了差距，但麦克罗伊以 3&amp;1 的比分击败了世界比洞赛冠军萨姆·伯恩斯，泰瑞尔·哈顿以 3&amp;2 的比分击败了公开赛冠军布莱恩·哈曼，夺得欧洲冠军距离胜利只有半分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;布鲁克斯·科普卡 (Brooks Koepka)、马克斯·霍马 (Max Homa) 和赞德·谢奥菲勒 (Xander Schauffele) 的胜利让比赛保持了活力，但当汤米·弗利特伍德 (Tommy Fleetwood) 赢得第 16 局时，以 2 比 2 领先与里基·福勒的比赛中，他得到了所需的半分，庆祝活动就可以开始了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦克罗伊觉得两年前在呼啸海峡，在击败谢奥菲勒之前遭受了三场惨败后，他让队友们失望了。单打比赛结束后，他在接受电视采访时泪流满面，承认自己迫不及待地想在罗马获得救赎。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位四届大满贯冠军在马可西蒙尼赢得了他的前三场比赛，但周六晚上输掉了最后一场四球赛，并因庆祝活动而与坎特利的球童乔·拉卡瓦发生了愤怒的争执&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/30/angry-rory-mcilroy -boils-over-in-ryder-cup-car-park-row-with-us-caddie&quot;>;溢出到停车场&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我需要它来给我加油今天，不要让它夺走美好的一周。”麦克罗伊说道。 “我觉得我利用了它来发挥自己的优势，并以不同程度的专注和决心，在某种程度上，它给整个团队带来了一点动力。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id =&quot;403a0ff28f30fed8eb0b4d016aa0fac087e76828&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/403a0ff28f30fed8eb0b4d016aa0fac087e76828/0_153_6370_3822/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;情绪化的汤米弗利特伍德（右）在 17 号果岭拥抱何塞·玛丽亚·奥拉萨瓦尔。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;情绪激动的汤米·弗利特伍德（右）在 17 号果岭拥抱何塞·玛丽亚·奥拉萨巴尔。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Andrew Medichini/美联社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;麦克罗伊强忍着泪水补充道：“我只是想为欧洲再赢一分。自从呼啸海峡之后，我对自己在那里的表现非常失望，所以来到这里为球队拿到四分对我来说意义重大。这是呼啸海峡之后的一次伟大的反弹。我们的团队令人难以置信。这是一支年轻的球队，我认为它会存在很长一段时间。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦克罗伊在 BBC 广播 5 直播中补充道：“昨天离开 18 号球场可能是我职业生涯中最愤怒的一次。我对美国佬说过，我认为所发生的事情是可耻的，我已经明确表示了这一点。但我需要让自己冷静下来，因为我可能会让它带我走上错误的道路，但我没有。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id=&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;guide&quot;>; &lt;details data-snippet-id=&quot;eab35d41-dbe9-4aec-9209-ae22c3b80688&quot; data-snippet-type=&quot;guide&quot;>; &lt;summary>; &lt;span>;快速指南&lt;/span >; &lt;h4>;如何注册体育突发新闻提醒？&lt;/h4>;&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot;>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;18px&quot; height=&quot;18px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 18 18&quot;>; &lt;路径 d=&quot;M8.2 0h1.6l.4 7.8 7.8.4v1.6l-7.8.4-.4 7.8H8.2l-.4-7.8L0 9.8V8.2l7.8-.4.4-7.8 z&quot; />; &lt;/svg>; 显示&lt;/span>; &lt;span>; &lt;svg width=&quot;32px&quot; height=&quot;32px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 32 32&quot;>; &lt;rect x=&quot;5&quot; y=&quot;15&quot; 宽度=&quot;22&quot; height=&quot;3&quot;>;&lt;/rect>; &lt;/svg>; 隐藏&lt;/span>; &lt;/span>; &lt;/summary>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>;从 iOS 下载 Guardian 应用iPhone 上的 App Store 或 Android 上的 Google Play 商店，只需搜索“The Guardian”即可。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;如果您已经安装了 Guardian 应用，请确保您使用的是最新版本。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>; li>;在 Guardian 应用中，点击右下角的“菜单”按钮，然后转到“设置”（齿轮图标），然后转到“通知”。&lt;/li>; &lt;li>;打开运动通知。&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt; /div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;footer>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; 这有帮助吗？ &lt;/div>;&lt;button value=&quot;like&quot; aria-label=&quot;Yes&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d= “M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1. 31&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt; /button>; &lt;button value=&quot;不喜欢&quot; aria-label=&quot;否&quot;>; &lt;svg width=&quot;40px&quot; height=&quot;40px&quot; viewbox=&quot;0 0 40 40&quot;>; &lt;path fill=&quot;#FFF&quot; d=&quot; M33.78 22.437l-4.228 13.98L27.93 37.5 5.062 34.14V15.503l7.8-1.517L24.354 2.5h1.624L28.9 5.426l-4.548 8.67h.107l10.477 1.3 1&quot; />; &lt;/svg>;&lt;/按钮>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div hide aria-role=&quot;alert&quot; aria-live=&quot;polite&quot;>; 感谢您的反馈。 &lt;/div>; &lt;/footer>; &lt;/details>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;拉姆承认他非常清楚对阵谢夫勒的比赛的重要性，谢夫勒在周六的四人二球赛中与科普卡并肩作战，以9&amp;7的比分惨败。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“我告诉自己我不会看，但很难不看记分牌，”拉姆说道。18 号，在舍夫勒 (Scheffler) 击出一个笨拙的切杆后，拉姆在 90 英尺处两推抓到小鸟。绿色的。我坐在那儿看着我的推杆（18 号洞），记分牌正好挡住了我的路。所以很难不让自己犹豫不决。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“但我认为我最后做得非常好。看到这些分数，我重新专注于手头的任务，并在最后打得很好。可惜没能赢，但我会赢一半。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 00:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[UK admits extra £330m a year in charges for post-Brexit animal and plant imports]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/oct/01/uk-admits-extra-330m-a-year-charges-post-brexit-food-imports]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T15:59:44Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c8ec0fee2e1d5a7ece4fcfc6397310f31d386d46/0_23_5100_3059 /master/5100.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=e17bddec99bc49e9d642fb644400eb57&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;荷兰草莓在南威尔士市场出售&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;政府承认这将使企业付出代价当明年对从欧盟进口的动植物产品实施新的脱欧后边境管制时，每年将产生 3.3 亿英镑的额外费用。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;内阁办公室国务部长露西·内维尔-罗尔夫 (Lucy Neville-Rolfe)，在致欧洲工党运动主席、工党议员斯特拉·克里西的信中，确认了预计的年度成本，并补充说英国需要更严格的边境管制，以“保护我们的国际声誉”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这将在很大程度上取决于内维尔-罗尔夫男爵夫人在回应 Creasy 时表示，“我们估计该模型的这些新成本为 3.3 亿英镑 [每年]总体而言，涵盖所有欧盟进口。自离开欧盟以来，我们的边境尚未实施全面的生物安全控制。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;食品和物流公司一再警告英国脱欧后的边境战略&lt;a href=&quot;https:// www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/jun/26/post-brexit-import-checks-risk-further-pushing-up-food-prices-industry-group&quot;>;风险进一步推高食品价格&lt;/a>;，由于通货膨胀猖獗，这些数字已经飙升。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;8 月，政府推迟了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/29/uk-brexit-checks -on-food-eu-delayed&quot;>;英国脱欧后第五次&lt;/a>;对抵达英国的食品、植物和动物产品进行检查，这意味着检查要到 2024 年 1 月底才会开始。&lt;/ p>; &lt;p>;政府表示，从 10 月底开始，延迟实施是在与业界进行谈判之后进行的，业界表示企业需要更多时间进行准备。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此举也被解读为对这一担忧的回应。开始检查将&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/jun/26/post-brexit-import-checks-risk-further-pushing-up-food-prices-industry-group “在生活成本危机期间，进一步加剧食品价格上涨&lt;/a>;，尽管政府表示，新边境战略对总体通胀的影响将“在三年内低于 0.2%”。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;内维尔-罗尔夫在信中表示，这些检查是必要的，因为自英国离开欧盟以来，“干预以应对对动物、植物和人类健康的威胁变得更具挑战性”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她说实施新的边境管制对于防止沙门氏菌和非洲猪瘟等疾病的国际传播至关重要，这些疾病&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/sep/10/german-farmers-face -possible-pig-culls-as-african-swine-fever-discovered&quot;>;在欧盟部分地区流行&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“低估巨大的&lt;a href=&quot; https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2022/apr/03/swine-fever-risk-if-uk-waives-checks-on-imports-from-eu-say-vets&quot;>;生命和健康成本这些疾病的爆发可能会给英国带来生计损失，”她说。 “它将帮助我们降低相当大的安全和生物安全威胁的风险和潜在影响。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Neville-Rolfe 表示，重大疾病爆发的成本可能比额外的损失产生更重大的财务影响。预计行业每年必须付出代价。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她引用了 2001 年爆发的口蹄疫为例，按 2022 年价格计算，该疾病造成的损失相当于 128 亿英镑。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其中，政府的成本为 48 亿英镑，而私营部门的费用为 80 亿英镑。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们还必须保护我们的国际声誉，”她说。 “对动植物产品持续缺乏进口管制，可能导致我们的贸易伙伴对我们的出口质量失去信心，特别是在疫情严重的情况下。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她表示，3.3 亿英镑中约有一半额外费用包括专家健康证明。不过，她表示，这比最初预计的 5.2 亿英镑的年度预算有所减少，直到今年早些时候政府决定实行不太繁重的边境管制。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Creasy 警告说，最终消费者会为食品支付更多费用。和产品，因为企业希望通过价格上涨来转嫁更高的成本。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“在进口食品方面苦苦挣扎的英国公司对这些费用别无选择，这意味着英国消费者可能不得不买单”，她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;从 1 月 30 日起，从欧盟进口的中风险动物产品、植物和植物产品以及高风险非动物源食品等物品将需要提供卫生证书，然后physical inspections of these goods at the UK border from the end of April next year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In the final phase, safety and security declarations for EU imports will come into force from the end of October 2024, with physical checks costing up to £43 a time.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, farmers and veterinary groups have &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.farmersguardian.com/news/4114103/border-check-plans-welcomed&quot;>; welcomed the new border checks &lt;/a>;saying that as well as protecting biosecurity it would help level terms of trade for British exporters who have faced full EU border checks since 1 January 2021.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 02 Oct 2023 00:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Robert Fico doubles down on pro-Russia stance after Slovakia election win]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/01/robert-fico-doubles-down-on-pro-russia-stance-after-slovakia-election-win]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T15:06:52Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/61adaec900aff7e5c98f4034adbb430bf134fe0f/0_0_7535_4523/master/7535.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=94a8cc05d7c0b349fa9d765d9f367bc6&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Robert Fico, the leader of the Slovakian Social Democracy (Smer) party, arrives at his party&#39;s headquarters in Bratislava, Slovakia, on Sunday.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Slovakia&#39;s populist former prime minister, Robert Fico, who campaigned on a pledge to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/slovakian-elections-qa-country-votes-after-four-pms-in-five-years&quot;>;end military aid to Ukraine&lt;/a>;, has said his position “has not changed” after his party&#39;s clear election win made him favourite to lead the country for a fourth time.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fico told reporters he was waiting for Slovakia&#39;s president to give him a mandate to start forming a government – expected on Monday – after officials said on Sunday that &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/sep/30/slovakia-election-2023-results-robert-fico-michal-simecka-peter-pellegrini-richard-sulik-latest-news&quot;>;Smer-SD had scored 22.9% in Saturday&#39;s vote&lt;/a>; with 99.98% of ballots counted.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fico said he was ready to open talks with other parties on forming a coalition government. “We&#39;re here, we&#39;re ready, we&#39;ve learned something, we&#39;re more experienced,” he said. “We have clear ideas; we have clear plans.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The 59-year-old, whose pro-Moscow stance has sparked fears Slovakia will join Hungary and its authoritarian leader &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/viktor-orban&quot;>;Viktor Orbán&lt;/a>; in challenging the EU&#39;s consensus on support for Kyiv, added: “People in Slovakia have bigger problems than Ukraine.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fico has leaned close to Orbán, who congratulated him on his victory on Sunday. “Guess who&#39;s back!” the Hungarian prime minister said on X, formerly known as Twitter. “Always good to work together with a patriot. Looking forward to it.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fico said his party was “not changing [its view] that we are prepared to help Ukraine in a humanitarian way … We are prepared to help with the reconstruction of the state. But you know our opinion on arming Ukraine.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The liberal, pro-western Progressive Slovakia (PS) party finished second on just under 18%, with Hlas – a spin-off from Smer formed after &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/mar/15/slovakias-prime-minister-robert-fico-resigns-journalist-murder&quot;>;Fico was forced to resign in 2018&lt;/a>; over political turmoil surrounding the murder of an investigative journalist and his fiancée – third on almost 15%.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;With his party set up as kingmaker, Peter Pellegrini, the Hlas leader, who has previously said his party favoured Smer, said on Sunday the priority in negotiations would be a stable coalition and legislative agenda. Talks could last days or weeks, he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;PS, which is liberal on environmental policies and LGBTQ+ and minority rights, and seeks deeper European integration, also suggested on Sunday it would approach Hlas. Its leader, Michal Šimečka, insisted he still saw a route to forming a ruling coalition.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We believe that this is very bad news for Slovakia,” the 39-year-old European parliament vice-chair said of Smer&#39;s victory. “And it would be even worse news if Robert Fico succeeds in forming a government.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Analysts said Slovakia&#39;s new ruling coalition would most likely be formed by Smer, Hlas and the nationalist, pro-Russian Slovak National Party (SNS), which would have a slim but functioning majority of 79 seats in the 150-seat parliament.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“If this transpires, a major assault on the rule of law is on the menu – Smer promised &#39;vengeance&#39;,” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/michal_ovadek/status/1708394055749558572&quot;>;said Michal Ovádek&lt;/a>;, a European politics specialist at University College London. “We will have to wait a few days to find out whether it materialises.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Milan Nič, of the German council on foreign relations, called Smer&#39;s victory a “stunning political revival for a veteran populist who is still entangled in corruption cases”, adding that Pellegrini would likely be offered the job of parliamentary speaker.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The key task for the west would be “not to lose Slovakia”, &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/MilanN_inBerlin/status/1708412188120035504&quot;>;Nič said&lt;/a>; on X. It would be vital to “engage constructively with Fico and manage cracks in support for Ukraine, as Hungary is no longer alone”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Radoslav Štefančík, an analyst from the University of Economics in Bratislava, said: “It can&#39;t be ruled out that Fico will be looking for a [European] partner who uses similar rhetoric - and that partner will be Viktor Orbán.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Analysts have, however, said Fico, who was pragmatic during previous mandates, may cool his rhetoric in a coalition with Hlas, which has said ammunition supplies to Ukraine are good for Slovakia&#39;s industry and backed the EU&#39;s stance on the invasion.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Several experts noted that one of the election&#39;s big surprises was the failure of the far-right Republika party, long seen as a potential Smer partner, to clear the 5% threshold for a seat in parliament, despite polling at between 7 and 10% for much of the year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In total, seven parties and groups scored high enough to enter parliament, including the centrist, anti-corruption OLaNO coalition that won the previous elections in 2020, the centrist Christian Democrats, and the rightwing SaS.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;President &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jun/20/slovakia-president-zuzana-caputova-says-she-will-not-run-for-re-election&quot;>;Zuzana Čaputová&lt;/a>;, a former member of Progressive Slovakia and a longtime political rival of Fico, said she would task him with forming a new government. “Tomorrow I will entrust the formation of the government to the winner of the election,” she said on Sunday.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 01 Oct 2023 23:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Tusk tells election rally in Warsaw: ‘change for the better is inevitable’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/01/donald-tusk-tells-election-rally-in-warsaw-change-for-the-better-is-inevitable-poland]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T14:31:14Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/18e5d6ae0c93faf87321b75d5e7636fb4fee502f/0_18_4633_2781/master/4633.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=32a02ac1fc9003797ad7f508e5d27708&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Donald Tusk speaks at an opposition rally in Warsaw with red-and-white flags in the foreground&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Huge crowds have gathered in central Warsaw at a rally organised by opposition leader Donald Tusk, two weeks before &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/01/polands-opposition-hopes-huge-rally-in-warsaw-will-swing-election&quot;>;a crucial election&lt;/a>; that will have major implications for the future political course of Poland and its role in Europe.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As a closely fought and vicious campaign enters its final straight, Tusk had called on supporters to rally in Warsaw to put on a show of strength and galvanise the opposition. Victory, he claimed, was in sight.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“A breakthrough moment is coming in the history of our homeland,” said Tusk on Sunday, addressing the crowds at the beginning of the rally, his words echoing through surrounding streets from banks of speakers set up in several locations. “Let no one among the ruling team have any illusions. Change for the better is inevitable,” he added.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Tusk claimed more than a million people had attended the march, dubbed the “March of a million hearts”, while Warsaw police said the number was about 100,000.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Large parts of the centre of Warsaw came to a standstill as people streamed through the streets carrying Polish and European Union flags, as well as banners with various jokey or angry slogans attacking the ruling Law and Justice (PiS) party.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“No one believed that such crowds and such emotions could happen again in our history. This is a sign of the great Polish revival,” said Tusk.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;3ce077dec1d0f3fd1b6b55a90666eb1f25d0f589&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/3ce077dec1d0f3fd1b6b55a90666eb1f25d0f589/0_496_5500_3302/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;The &#39;March of a million hearts&#39; rally in Warsaw, Poland.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;The &#39;March of a million hearts&#39; rally in Warsaw, Poland. &lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Kacper Pempel/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Tusk was the Polish prime minister between 2007 and 2014 before leaving Poland to become president of the European Council. He has returned to Polish politics to lead the opposition campaign in what he has claimed is the last chance to save Polish democracy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;PiS came to power in 2015 and have pursued a rightwing populist agenda combined with increased social spending, winning much support in rural areas. At the same time, they have curtailed rights for women and minorities and been accused of democratic backsliding.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Polls suggest PiS will do slightly better than Tusk&#39;s Civic Coalition, and the final result is likely to come down to the performance of several smaller parties and the arithmetic around coalition building.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;PiS leaders held their own event in the city of Katowice on Sunday, timed to coincide with the Tusk march. They continued a campaign strategy of portraying the opposition as foreign stooges, using Tusk&#39;s years in Brussels to claim he now answers to German interests.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This vote is not only about what Poland will look like. It is about whether Poland will exist at all,” claimed the prime minister, Mateusz Morawiecki, brandishing a file he said contained damaging information about Tusk, who had a “German vision” for Poland&#39;s future.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A large part of Tusk&#39;s campaign has been about reclaiming the language of patriotism for the opposition, leading to the red-and-white hearts that have become a symbol of the campaign. On Sunday, thousands in attendance at the rally were waving red-and-white Polish flags.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I see a sea of red and white banners … We all share the view that our red-and-white homeland can be home to free people again,” said Tusk.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The years of PiS rule have seen a takeover of public media, increasing friction with Brussels and the introduction of some of Europe&#39;s harshest anti-abortion laws.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Rafał Trzaskowski, the Civic Coalition mayor of Warsaw, also addressed the rally, saying he hoped that the elections would lead to a more “open and tolerant” Poland.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We are marching so that children do not have to watch their mothers being beaten because they are fighting for their rights … so that no one attacks kids with rainbow tote bags who are fighting for their rights,” said Trzaskowski.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While the size of the rally will doubtless energise opposition forces as they enter the final stage of campaigning, most observers say the final outcome of the election is still impossible to predict with confidence.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It&#39;s amazing to see so many happy, smiling people in one place and to get a sense of what a different place Poland could be,” said 41-year-old Joanna from Wrocław, who travelled to Warsaw with her two teenage daughters to attend the rally. “But I&#39;m still really worried that PiS can win again, and then I will be worried for me, but especially worried for these two and their future in this country,” she said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Additional reporting by Katarzyna Piasecka&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 01 Oct 2023 22:52:02 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[At least 13 people killed in Spanish nightclub fire]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/01/spanish-nightclub-fire-teatre-murcia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T13:37:02Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/51ce074b18081bc1348d7fa9f0090db7321c2147/0_325_4420_2652/master/4420.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fc7f5db72c921417cd4f38df19c0b1f2&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A firefighter walks past the blackened facade of the Teatre nightclub in Murcia, southeastern Spain.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;At least 13 people were killed in a fire in a Spanish nightclub on Sunday morning, authorities said, with fears the toll could still rise as rescue workers sift through the debris.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The fire broke out in the two-storey Teatre nightclub, also called Fonda Milagros, in the city of Murcia in southeastern Spain in the early hours of the morning.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The emergency services said on X, formerly known as Twitter, that firefighters were continuing to work at the scene and had not ruled out “the possibility of finding more victims”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;José Ballesta, the mayor of Murcia, said the fire had broken out at about 6am local time (4am GMT) and was “extremely serious”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He told press at the scene that “there are still bodies to be pulled out” from the rubble, which he said was a complicated task given the risk of collapse.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Firefighters dispatched to the scene at 7am were able to extinguish the fire by 8am, he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Photos released by the emergency services show water hoses from fire trucks spraying the blackened facade of the club. Thick smoke could be seen billowing from the roof of the building.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Authorities said four people were injured – two women aged 22 and 25 and two men in their forties – all suffering with smoke inhalation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Diego Seral, the national police spokeperson, said that a birthday party was being held at the club on Saturday night.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“According to initial information, the fire broke out on the first floor,” he told the radio station Onda Regional de Murcia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Forensic and judicial police experts had been deployed to the nightclub to investigate the cause, the national police service said on X.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Video footage released by the city&#39;s firefighting brigade shows the firefighters holding a long hose approaching flames inside the venue, passing bar tables that still have drinks placed on them.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;More than 40 firefighters and 12 emergency vehicles were attending the scene, authorities said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/pedro-s-nchez&quot;>;Pedro Sánchez&lt;/a>;, the prime minister of Spain, voiced “solidarity with the victims and relatives of the tragic fire in a Murcia nightclub”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The city&#39;s town hall said it “deeply regrets” the accident and offered condolences to those affected.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The mayor announced that three days of mourning would be held, and set up a reception base for the relatives of victims.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Forty people were injured in 2017 in a packed nightclub on Spain&#39;s holiday island of Tenerife when a floor collapsed.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;And in 1990, 43 people died in a fire at a nightclub in Spain&#39;s northeastern city of Zaragoza.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 01 Oct 2023 21:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Kosovan government calls on Serbia to pull all troops from border]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/01/kosovo-government-serbia-troops-border-withdrawal]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T12:29:31Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/107d887c37fd046f9fbc3852860456371485b48e/0_365_5472_3283/master/5472.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=06a969ee8392570c6c15277e53d7027d&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Kosovan police carrying machine guns stand next to an armoured vehicle on a country road&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Kosovo has demanded that Serbia pull its troops back from their common border and warned it was ready to protect its territorial integrity, after the US warned of punitive measures against Belgrade and Serbia&#39;s president insisted he “does not want war”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We call on … Serbia to immediately withdraw all troops from the border with Kosovo,” the Kosovan government said, demanding that Belgrade “demilitarise” 48 forward military and police bases, “which pose a permanent threat to our country”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Tensions between the two countries have been high since last Sunday when well-armed Serbian paramilitaries ambushed a Kosovan police patrol, killing a police officer. Three Serbian gunmen were killed in the ensuing battle, near the village of Banjska.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The gun battle prompted fresh international concern over the stability of Kosovo, which has an ethnic Albanian majority and declared independence from Serbia in 2008 after a guerrilla uprising and a 1999 Nato intervention.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Serbia pulled back some of its troops on Saturday after warnings from Washington that it could face punitive measures over what the White House called an “unprecedented” buildup of Serbian troops and armour on the border.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/30/serbia-pulls-some-troops-back-from-kosovo-border-after-warning-from-us&quot;>;Serbia pulls some troops back from Kosovo border after warning from US&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The Serbian president, Aleksandar Vučić, said in a statement to the Financial Times that he had given the order for the part withdrawal, saying any military action would be counterproductive and adding: “Serbia does not want war.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A Kosovan government official confirmed the removal of some troops and equipment that had been moved into positions around the border over the past five days, but a significant force remains permanently based in the area.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The deployment of Serbian troops along the border with Kosovo is the next step by Serbia to threaten the territorial integrity of our country,” the Kosovan government said in its statement, issued late on Saturday after the part withdrawal.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This deployment also includes the deployment of anti-aircraft systems and heavy artillery.” It added: “Kosovo, in coordination with international partners, is more determined than ever to protect its territorial integrity.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Pristina government said it had “maintained continuous contact with the US and with EU countries regarding this serious threat from Serbia, and the reaction of the US … has been immediate and direct”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Friday the US said it was monitoring Serbian deployment along the Kosovo border. The US secretary of state, Antony Blinken, called Vučić to demand “​​immediate de-escalation” and a return to a previous agreement to normalise relations with Kosovo.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Vučić said Blinken had told him there could be US measures against Serbia if he did not comply. Nato, which has 4,500 troops in Kosovo, has since authorised the reinforcement of its Kfor peacekeeping force with hundreds of British troops.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Unease in Kosovo&#39;s troubled north has been building for months since the prime minister, Albin Kurti, sparked protests and riots this spring by installing ethnic Albanian mayors in four Serb-majority municipalities there.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;EU-sponsored negotiations between Kosovo and Serbia&#39;s leaders have repeatedly broken down and appear all but dead in the water after last Sunday&#39;s fighting.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The analyst Dimitar Bechev &lt;a href=&quot;https://carnegieeurope.eu/strategiceurope/90656&quot;>;said in a column for Carnegie Europe&lt;/a>;: “The more such incidents occur, the less likely it is that Serbia and Kosovo will be willing or able to compromise. The EU will not be able to fix the problem – perhaps only manage it.”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 01 Oct 2023 20:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Autumn heat continues in Europe after record-breaking September]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/oct/01/autumn-heat-continues-in-europe-after-record-breaking-september]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-01T11:39:51Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d67e849ee44266f85de8f59b7f4963b9de68ac20/0_281_6000_3600 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b887ec0352803405d3cc8abf88dbf6ed&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;九月初，巴黎市中心的塞纳河上，妇女们在喷雾机下行走，以降温。&lt;/ div>;&lt;p>;奥地利、比利时、法国、德国、波兰和瑞士都经历了有记录以来最热的九月，反常的高温将持续到十月，这可能是人类历史上最热的一年。&lt;/p >; &lt;p>;预计周日法国西南部气温为 31 摄氏度（88 华氏度），巴黎气温为 28 摄氏度，法国气象局法国气象局表示，9 月平均气温为 21.5 摄氏度，比正常水平高出 3.5 摄氏度至 3.6 摄氏度。气象学家 Christine Berne 表示，这使其成为自 1900 年有记录以来最热的 9 月，气温升高了 1 摄氏度以上。她补充说，在一些地区，与 9 月平均值的偏差过去三十年里，气温超过 4 摄氏度，有时超过 6 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;法国气象局表示，在这个“特殊”的月份里，全国各地打破了“很多”月度记录，平均气温高于德国气象局 DWD 表示，今年 9 月是国家有记录以来最热的 9 月，比 1961-1990 年的基线高出近 4 摄氏度。 ，而比利时 19 摄氏度的平均气温也比正常水平高出近 4 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;比利时皇家气象研究所的 David Dehenauw 表示：“这里的 9 月也比 7 月和 8 月更热，这是自 1961 年以来从未发生过的情况.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“比利时从未经历过如此温暖的 9 月份。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;波兰气象研究所也宣布 9 月份气温比平均水平高 3.6 摄氏度，是自 9 月份以来最热的月份。记录始于 100 多年前，奥地利和瑞士当局也是如此。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;上个月上半月发生的史无前例的热浪推动了月平均温度异常高，法国在这次热浪中记录了有史以来的 9 月份最高气温维埃纳省中西部气温 38.8 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/ sep/28/europes-local-olive-oil-supply-runs-almost-dry-after-summer-of-extreme-weather&quot;>;欧洲橄榄油供应在干旱和奇怪的冰雹之后耗尽&lt;/a>;&lt;/与此同时，在西班牙南部，科尔多瓦附近的蒙托罗于 9 月 5 日记录了欧洲有记录以来 9 月份最高气温——45.7 摄氏度，本周末气温达到 35 摄氏度。 .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟气候监测机构9月初表示，北半球夏季全球气温&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/06/summer- of-2023-hottest-recorded-in-wake-up-call-to-cut-carbon-emission&quot;>;有记录以来最热&lt;/a>;。哥白尼气候变化服务机构还预计 2023 年将是人类经历过的最热的一年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;科学家表示，人类活动驱动的气候变化正在推高全球气温，全球气温较之前升高约 1.2 摄氏度。工业水平。地球气候系统的破坏使得热浪、干旱、野火和风暴等极端天气事件更加频繁和强烈。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;法国气象局伯尔尼表示，热浪也发生在通常的夏季高温月份之外。七月和八月。 “按照政府间气候变化专门委员会 (IPPC) 的模型，我们会在春季和 9 月甚至 10 月看到它们，”她说。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 01 Oct 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>